Privacy Policy Updated: September 25, 2023
Welcome to the GFK Digital Asset Trading Platform (referred to as "GFK" or "we"). We highly value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. To ensure that you fully understand our policies and practices regarding the collection, use, and protection of your information, please read this Privacy Policy carefully.
I. Introduction
1.1 This policy is designed to inform you about how we collect, use, store, and protect your personal information. We adhere to the relevant laws and regulations of Lithuania and work diligently to safeguard your privacy.
1.2 "GFK" is the English name for the GFK Digital Asset Trading Platform. In this policy, "GFK" or "we" refers to our platform. "You" refers to the users of our services.
II. Types of Information Collected
2.1 We may collect the following types of information:
(a) Personal Identification Information: Such as your name, identification number, email address, contact address, and phone number.
(b) Financial Information: Such as your bank account number, transaction records, digital asset addresses, and more.
(c) Technical Information: We may automatically collect technical information about your visits to our website or use of our applications, including IP addresses, device information, browser type, access dates, and times, among others.
(d) User-Generated Content: This includes transaction information, comments, questions, and other content you provide on our platform.
(e) Other Information: We may collect other types of information as required by applicable laws or with your consent. 2.2 You have the right to choose whether to provide certain types of information, but this may affect your ability to use some of our services.
III. Use of Information
3.1 We may use your information for the following purposes:
(a) Service Provision: This includes processing transactions, verifying identities, providing customer support, and managing your account.
(b) Regulatory Requirements: Complying with applicable laws and court orders, preventing fraud, and money laundering.
(c) Service Improvement: Analyzing user needs and behaviors to enhance our products and services.
(d) Marketing: Sending promotional and marketing information to you with your consent.
(e) Security Protection: Protecting your and our security, including preventing unauthorized access and data breaches.
3.2 We only share your information as permitted by law, such as with our partners, regulatory agencies, and law enforcement authorities. We take appropriate measures to ensure the protection of your information.
IV. Information Storage and Security
4.1 Information Storage: We store your information on secure servers and employ necessary technical and organizational measures to protect it from unauthorized access, loss, damage, or disclosure. We regularly review and update security measures to address evolving threats.
4.2 Account Access Control: Access to your account requires personal password verification. Please safeguard your account information and do not share your password or authorize others to use your account. If you suspect a security breach or password compromise, please notify us immediately so we can take necessary steps to protect your account.
V. Privacy Rights Protection
5.1 Information Access and Correction: You have the right to inquire about, access, and correct your personal information at any time. If you need to access or correct your information, please log in to your account or contact our customer support team, and we will promptly respond to your request.
5.2 Withdrawal of Consent: If you have previously consented to our processing of your information but later decide to withdraw your consent, please contact us. Please note that withdrawing consent may affect your ability to use our services, but it will not impact the processing of information you have already provided.
5.3 Information Deletion: In certain cases, in accordance with applicable laws and regulations, you may request the deletion of your personal information. We will fulfill your request within the bounds of the law.
5.4 Privacy Officer: If you have any questions, concerns, or complaints about this policy or your privacy rights, or if you need to exercise the rights mentioned above, please contact our Privacy Officer. We are committed to assisting you with these matters.
We appreciate your attention to our Privacy Policy and your understanding. By continuing to use GFK services, you agree to the terms and conditions of this policy. If you have any further questions or need additional assistance, please feel free to contact our customer support team.
VI. Policy Updates
6.1 We may periodically update this policy to reflect changes in the law and improvements to our services. Any significant changes will be posted on our website.
Thank you for reading our Privacy Policy. We value your privacy and are committed to maintaining and protecting your privacy rights. If you have any other questions or need further assistance, please don't hesitate to contact our customer support team.

(c) Technical Information: We may automatically collect technical information about your visits to our website or use of our applications, including IP addresses, device information, browser type, access dates, and times, among others.
(d) User-Generated Content: This includes transaction information, comments, questions, and other content you provide on our platform.
(e) Other Information: We may collect other types of information as required by applicable laws or with your consent. 2.2 You have the right to choose whether to provide certain types of information, but this may affect your ability to use some of our services.
III. Use of Information
3.1 We may use your information for the following purposes:
(a) Service Provision: This includes processing transactions, verifying identities, providing customer support, and managing your account.
(b) Regulatory Requirements: Complying with applicable laws and court orders, preventing fraud, and money laundering.
(c) Service Improvement: Analyzing user needs and behaviors to enhance our products and services.
(d) Marketing: Sending promotional and marketing information to you with your consent.
(e) Security Protection: Protecting your and our security, including preventing unauthorized access and data breaches.
3.2 We only share your information as permitted by law, such as with our partners, regulatory agencies, and law enforcement authorities. We take appropriate measures to ensure the protection of your information.
IV. Information Storage and Security
4.1 Information Storage: We store your information on secure servers and employ necessary technical and organizational measures to protect it from unauthorized access, loss, damage, or disclosure. We regularly review and update security measures to address evolving threats.
4.2 Account Access Control: Access to your account requires personal password verification. Please safeguard your account information and do not share your password or authorize others to use your account. If you suspect a security breach or password compromise, please notify us immediately so we can take necessary steps to protect your account.
V. Privacy Rights Protection
5.1 Information Access and Correction: You have the right to inquire about, access, and correct your personal information at any time. If you need to access or correct your information, please log in to your account or contact our customer support team, and we will promptly respond to your request.
5.2 Withdrawal of Consent: If you have previously consented to our processing of your information but later decide to withdraw your consent, please contact us. Please note that withdrawing consent may affect your ability to use our services, but it will not impact the processing of information you have already provided.
5.3 Information Deletion: In certain cases, in accordance with applicable laws and regulations, you may request the deletion of your personal information. We will fulfill your request within the bounds of the law.
5.4 Privacy Officer: If you have any questions, concerns, or complaints about this policy or your privacy rights, or if you need to exercise the rights mentioned above, please contact our Privacy Officer. We are committed to assisting you with these matters.
We appreciate your attention to our Privacy Policy and your understanding. By continuing to use GFK services, you agree to the terms and conditions of this policy. If you have any further questions or need additional assistance, please feel free to contact our customer support team.
VI. Policy Updates
6.1 We may periodically update this policy to reflect changes in the law and improvements to our services. Any significant changes will be posted on our website.
Thank you for reading our Privacy Policy. We value your privacy and are committed to maintaining and protecting your privacy rights. If you have any other questions or need further assistance, please don't hesitate to contact our customer support team.
